Software Engineer 2
What if your job description were simply make tomorrow better? That’s the essence of roles within our Bing Team. Every day, we bring an insatiable curiosity to the table, challenging ourselves to reimagine what is and what can be. We build on what’s come before to create what’s next. We drive machine intelligence. We help shape the future. We empower billions of people around the globe. 

Do you want to work on a development team that helps millions of internet users get the best Bing search experience? We, Whole Page team at Bing, are looking for strong enthusiastic developers to join us to create the best search experience for end users!

The Whole Page Team develops advanced technologies to enable best whole page experience for the search results for various segments. We are a team building end-to-end experiences, algorithmically determining the best whole page composition based on the query and device, leading to quicker task completion and delighting our end-users. The work includes offline data mining/processing, runtime infrastructure work, and machine learning techniques to improve the quality of Bing search experience on various devices.   We aspire to accelerate the pace of innovation for search experience through very talented people like you. 
  
We are looking for someone that: 
• Is strong in both engineering and algorithm design. 
• Is able to take on broad technical initiatives, drive and work on algorithm and architecture design, execute and deliver results. 
• Is passionate about coding, quality and teamwork. 
• Is passionate about driving innovation based on end user metrics and KPIs, shipping product with fast-pace. 
• Is willing to ship end-to-end features and release all the parts of the feature independently. 
• Is able to do detailed data analysis and improve the user experience iteratively.

Primary responsibilities of the position:
• Design, develop and improve algorithms to improve data quality and power rich user experiences
• Design, develop and ship runtime infrastructure to power end-to-end experience.
• Work with large scale of web and user data, build highly efficient data mining and generation pipeline 
• Aid in monitoring our live site and ensuring rock-solid reliability and performance for our millions of users 
• Ensure that our products ship fast and with high quality
• Working effectively with the other disciplines within Bing to help us become the best search engine on the web

This job requires strong technical skills. You must have the following skills and experience:
• 3+ years of software development experience.
• BS or higher degree in CS or related engineering field.
• Experience in online services development
• Experience in machine learning techniques preferred

